POSITION PURPOSE

The role is to provide support to the International Office Manager (IOM) in designing, planning, executing & managing the Department’s mobility programs as well as operating BUV’s international mobility student support services.

AREAS OF RESPONSIBILITY

• Provide support to the IOM in designing, planning mobility programmes;

• Manage/provide direct consultations to prospective students and stakeholders (partners,
parents…) about BUV mobility opportunities as assigned by IOM;

• Coordinate with relevant Departments (or stakeholders) to ensure smooth operation of student mobility programmes (including pre-admission process, pre-departure briefing, visa application procedures, on-arrival procedures, post-mobility procedures; …

• Implement mobility programme and activities within approved budget of each programme;

WHAT YOU WILL DO
As a Legal Supervisor at Pizza 4P’s, you will play a key role in managing and providing legal support across both domestic and overseas operations. You will report directly to the Legal & Compliance Manager and oversee legal activities within your assigned regions. Your responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
• Provide day-to-day legal support to business units and related departments;
• Review, draft, and negotiate a wide range of contracts (commercial, lease, supply, service, manufacturing, etc.);
• Support corporate governance and compliance for entities in Vietnam and abroad;
• Advise on business operations, internal policies, and compliance frameworks;
• Support overseas expansion projects, primarily related to restaurant openings in other countries and other legal matters arising from such operations;
• Provide legal support for manufacturing activities, including factory operations, supplier agreements, food safety compliance, and product quality control;
• Coordinate with external counsels and local partners to ensure compliance with local laws and internal standards;
• Manage and mentor the assigned Legal Specialist to ensure high-quality and timely deliverables;
• Handle dispute resolution, risk mitigation, and communication with authorities when necessary;
• Ensure consistency in legal documentation, procedures, and reporting across all jurisdictions.

Responsibilities
● Plan and deliver lesson plans aligned to the provided curricula (KIDS, YOUNG LEARNERS, IELTS, SAT, COMMUNICATION, DEBATE, etc.);
● Actively monitor individual and whole-class performance during learning sessions;
● Assign coursework/homework, mark promptly, and provide specific, actionable feedback focused on language targets and success criteria;
● Administer periodic assessments to track learning progress; analyze results to adjust instruction and intervention plans;
● Identify learners needing support and provide differentiated tasks for different groups of students; communicate progress to stakeholders as needed;
● Compile progress reports (language skills, participation, compliance) after scheduled assessments, with recommendations for next steps;
● Attend team meetings, workshops, peer observations and feedback/coaching cycles; implement agreed action points in subsequent lessons;
● Review and refine teaching materials for clarity and learning impact; support the creation/adaptation of lesson resources.
Perks
● Join an education-focused culture where academic integrity is non-negotiable;
● Fixed schedule with a 100% booking rate for steady income and job security;
● Participate in structured training on pedagogical skills, professionalism, and 21st-century competencies;
● Grow on a clear, merit-based career ladder with competency rubrics, mentorship, and promotion reviews;
● Receive personalized support for language-skill development when required.

